.SH "NAME"
theme \- extensible theme orchestrator for shell environments
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBtheme\fP [\fIOPTIONS\fP] [dark|light]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBtheme\fP detects the system appearance (dark or light mode) and orchestrates
theme configuration across multiple tools via an extensible provider/handler
system.
.sp
The command performs three steps:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 1.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 1." 4.2
.\}
\fBDetection\fP \- Determines system appearance (dark/light) using OS\-native
methods
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 2.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 2." 4.2
.\}
\fBProvider\fP \- Calls a user\-registered provider function that maps appearance
to theme variables (e.g., THEME_VARIANT, THEME_ACCENT)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 3.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 3." 4.2
.\}
\fBHandlers\fP \- Calls all registered handler functions that configure
individual tools using the exported theme variables
.RE
.sp
Providers and handlers are auto\-discovered by function name prefix or loaded
from configuration files.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-\-detect\fP
.RS 4
Only detect and print the system appearance (dark or light). Does not run
the provider or handlers.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-list\fP
.RS 4
List the discovered provider and all registered handlers.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
.RS 4
Suppress warning messages.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Show help message and exit.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-version\fP
.RS 4
Show version information and exit.
.RE
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.sp
\fBdark\fP | \fBlight\fP
.RS 4
Override the detected appearance. When specified, detection is skipped and
this value is passed directly to the provider.
.RE
.SH "DETECTION"
.sp
\fBtheme\fP uses OS\-native methods to detect appearance:
.sp
\fBmacOS\fP
.RS 4
Reads \f(CRAppleInterfaceStyle\fP via \f(CRdefaults read \-g AppleInterfaceStyle\fP.
Returns "dark" if set to "Dark", otherwise "light".
.RE
.sp
\fBLinux (GNOME/Unity)\fP
.RS 4
Queries \f(CRorg.gnome.desktop.interface color\-scheme\fP via \f(CRgsettings\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fBLinux (KDE Plasma)\fP
.RS 4
Reads \f(CRColorScheme\fP from \f(CRkdeglobals\fP via \f(CRkreadconfig5\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fBLinux (XFCE)\fP
.RS 4
Queries \f(CR/Net/ThemeName\fP via \f(CRxfconf\-query\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fBWindows (WSL/Cygwin)\fP
.RS 4
Queries \f(CRAppsUseLightTheme\fP from Windows registry via \f(CRreg.exe\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fBFallback\fP
.RS 4
Uses \f(CRTHEME\fP environment variable if set, otherwise defaults to "light".
.RE
.SH "PROVIDERS"
.sp
A provider is a shell function that receives the detected appearance and
exports theme variables for handlers to consume.
.SS "Provider Contract"
.sp
Providers must:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Be named with prefix \f(CRtheme_provider_\fP (e.g., \f(CRtheme_provider_catppuccin\fP)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Accept two arguments: \f(CR$1\fP = appearance (dark|light), \f(CR$2\fP = source
(detected|default|override)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Export \f(CRTHEME\fP and any additional variables handlers need
.RE
.SS "Provider Discovery"
.sp
Providers are discovered in order:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 1.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 1." 4.2
.\}
Functions matching \f(CRtheme_provider_*\fP in current shell
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 2.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 2." 4.2
.\}
Functions defined in \f(CR~/.config/theme/provider.sh\fP
.RE
.sp
Only the first discovered provider is used.
.SS "Example Provider"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
theme_provider_catppuccin() {
  local appearance="$1"\&  # dark | light
  local source="$2"\&      # detected | default | override

  export THEME="$appearance"

  case "$appearance" in
    dark)\&  export THEME_VARIANT=mocha ;;
    light) export THEME_VARIANT=latte ;;
  esac

  export THEME_ACCENT=blue
}
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "HANDLERS"
.sp
Handlers are shell functions that configure individual tools using the theme
variables exported by the provider.
.SS "Handler Contract"
.sp
Handlers must:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Be named with prefix \f(CRtheme_handler_\fP (e.g., \f(CRtheme_handler_bat\fP)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Read configuration from \f(CRTHEME_*\fP environment variables
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Configure their target tool (export vars, write config files, etc.)
.RE
.SS "Handler Discovery"
.sp
Handlers are discovered from:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 1.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 1." 4.2
.\}
Functions matching \f(CRtheme_handler_*\fP in current shell
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 2.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 2." 4.2
.\}
Functions defined in scripts under \f(CR~/.config/theme/handlers.d/*.sh\fP
.RE
.sp
All discovered handlers are executed in alphabetical order.
.SS "Example Handlers"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
theme_handler_bat() {
  export BAT_THEME="Catppuccin ${THEME_VARIANT^}"
}

theme_handler_vivid() {
  export LS_COLORS="$(vivid generate catppuccin\-${THEME_VARIANT})"
}

theme_handler_fzf() {
  if [[ "$THEME" == "dark" ]]; then
    export FZF_DEFAULT_OPTS="\-\-color=dark"
  else
    export FZF_DEFAULT_OPTS="\-\-color=light"
  fi
}
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "External Handler Files"
.sp
Handlers can be defined in separate files under \f(CR~/.config/theme/handlers.d/\fP:
.sp
.B ~/.config/theme/handlers.d/bottom.sh
.br
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
#!/usr/bin/env bash
theme_handler_bottom() {
  export BTM_CONFIG_FILE="$HOME/.config/bottom/themes/${THEME_VARIANT}.toml"
}
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "FILES"
.sp
\fB~/.config/theme/config.sh\fP
.RS 4
User configuration file. Sourced before provider/handler discovery.
Can be used to set default variables or configure behavior.
.RE
.sp
\fB~/.config/theme/provider.sh\fP
.RS 4
Custom provider definition. Sourced during provider discovery.
.RE
.sp
\fB~/.config/theme/handlers.d/\fP.sh*
.RS 4
External handler scripts. All \f(CR.sh\fP files in this directory are sourced
during handler discovery.
.RE
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.sp
\fBTHEME\fP
.RS 4
Current theme appearance (dark or light). Set by the provider. Can also
be set manually to override detection.
.RE
.sp
\fBTHEME_VARIANT\fP
.RS 4
Theme variant name (e.g., mocha, latte). Set by the provider.
.RE
.sp
\fBTHEME_ACCENT\fP
.RS 4
Accent color (e.g., blue, pink). Set by the provider.
.RE
.sp
Additional \f(CRTHEME_*\fP variables may be exported by custom providers.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.sp
\fB0\fP
.RS 4
Success.
.RE
.sp
\fB1\fP
.RS 4
Runtime error (no provider found, detection failed).
.RE
.sp
\fB2\fP
.RS 4
Usage error (invalid arguments).
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
Detect appearance and apply theme to all handlers
.RS 4
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
theme
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
Force dark mode
.RS 4
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
theme dark
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
Only detect appearance (no handlers)
.RS 4
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
theme \-\-detect
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
List discovered provider and handlers
.RS 4
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
theme \-\-list
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.SS "Shell Integration"
.sp
Add to shell configuration for automatic theming on startup:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
# ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc
source /path/to/theme.sh

# Define provider
theme_provider_catppuccin() {
  local appearance="$1"
  export THEME="$appearance"
  case "$appearance" in
    dark)\&  export THEME_VARIANT=mocha ;;
    light) export THEME_VARIANT=latte ;;
  esac
  export THEME_ACCENT=blue
}

# Define handlers
theme_handler_bat() {
  export BAT_THEME="Catppuccin ${THEME_VARIANT^}"
}

theme_handler_vivid() {
  export LS_COLORS="$(vivid generate catppuccin\-${THEME_VARIANT})"
}

# Apply theme on shell startup
theme
.fam
.fi
